OL,3,CIncreasing gender pay gap for head
OL,4,Cteachers ` report
OL,6,FThe gap for primary heads also
OL,7,Fincreased, meaning women were paid
OL,8,F#2,608 less on average than their male
OL,9,Fcounterparts.
OL,11,FThe pay gap widens with age and
OL,12,Fseniority, said the union, adding that
OL,13,Ffor female head teachers aged 60 and
OL,14,Fover, the difference has reached an
OL,15,Faverage of #14,352.
OL,17,FThe NAHT pointed out that the majority
OL,18,Fof the education workforce is female,
OL,19,Fwith 77% of teachers and 68% of head
OL,20,Fteachers being women.
